I don't. Everything above looks right. Could we enable the instrumentation log? I'd like to see whether the problem is that
- IntelliJ isn't sending completion request (unlikely),
- server is responding at all,
- server responds but with an empty list, or
- server throws an exception.

> Could we enable the instrumentation log?

How is that done?

In IntelliJ:
1. select "Find Action..." from the "Help" menu,
2. search for "Registry" and select "Registry...",
3. edit "dart.server.additional.arguments" to include "--instrumentation-log-file=" followed by the path to where you want the file to be written,
4. click "Close",
5. restart the analysis server, and reproduce the invalid behavior (preferably after server has stopped analyzing your code).

I tried on Windows, and it works with Intellij Idea 2019.1, and with updated Flutter.

So, I think that the problem is that Flutter and Dart SDK version is older than expected.

https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/releases/tag/2.2.0-dev.2.0

Bumping to a P0 while to track down why this is happening.

I was able to reproduce the issue on the Flutter stable channel but switching to the dev channel with

`flutter channel dev && flutter upgrade`

seems to have fixed the issue for me. Does this work for others? /cc @MichelMelhem @ipereto @gabrielnemeth 

The longer explanation is that flutter 1.2.1 bundles a version of analysis server which implements a slightly different version of the not-yet-imported completions spec than the Dart IntelliJ plugin client can consume.

Thanks all for the reports of this issue; we're working on having a fix out as soon as possible.

In the meantime, you can work around the issue by switching to a newer Flutter SDK (either `dev` or `master` will work). As @lambdabaa says above,

```
flutter channel dev && flutter upgrade
```
Dart plugin with the fix has been released. Try Help -> Check for updates.
